factors = ['rank', 'studentPopulation', 'totalStudentPop', 'undergradPop',
        'percentOfStudentsFinAid', 'percentOfStudentsGrant']

for i in factors:
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize = (15, 5))
    plt.title(i)
    sns.histplot(data = df[i], bins = 20, kde = True, ax = axs[0], color = '#8E1600');
    sns.boxplot(data = df[i], ax = axs[1], palette = 'Reds', fliersize = 1)
    plt.show()

def to_geojson(row):
    'Transform hex_id ainto geojson object.'
    geometry = {'type': 'Polygon', 'coordinates': [h3.h3_to_geo_boundary(h=row['hex_id'],
                                                                        geo_json=True)]}
    return geojson.Feature(id = row['hex_id'], geometry = geometry, properties = {'totalStudentPop': row['totalStudentPop']})
